docs.lead_paragraph: The health classes at my son's high school have been walking around carrying water bottles with tennis-ball heads that are dressed in babylike outfits. It is the school's way of showing teenagers that real infants are a responsibility for which they are not prepared; they are required to keep their "babies" with them at all times, filling out logs of how often the newborns are fed, changed and soothed back to sleep.
docs.abstract: There are faux-babies designed not to dissuade users from parenthood but toward it.
docs.snippet: There are faux-babies designed not to dissuade users from parenthood but toward it.
